  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of emergency healthcare to the victims of earthquake in SER of Afghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide emergency healthcare and WASH services to earthquake victims. This WHO project provides 1) 43,200 people with primary healthcare consultations, 2) 25,920 people with mental health and/or psycho-social support, 3) 7,560 people with surgical procedures for trauma, 4) 3,600 people with acute watery diarrhea treatment, and 5) 5,334 people with safe water among other activities. The project provides life-saving assistance to 183,911 people, including 58,851 women, 53,333 men, 71,727 children, and 15,448 persons with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
